ds-winners-2018|title=The Game Awards 2018: Here are all the winners|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|author=Christopher Grant|date=6 December 2018|accessdate=9 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207114102/https://www.polygon.com/game-awards-tga/2018/12/6/18130000/the-game-awards-winners-2018|archive-date=7 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Fun & Serious Game Festival|Titanium Awards]]\n| Best Artistic Design\n| {{Nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.funandseriousgamefestival.com/awards/|title=Titanium Awards 2018|website=[[Fun & Serious Game Festival]]|accessdate=7 November 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707230958/https://en.funandseriousgamefestival.com/awards/|archivedate=7 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-12-10-red-dead-redemption-2-wins-best-game-at-fun-and-serious-festival-awards|title=Red Dead Redemption 2 wins Best Game at Fun & Serious Festival Awards|website=GamesIndustry.biz|author=Matthew Handrahan|date=10 December 2018|accessdate=7 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211012223/https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-12-10-red-dead-redemption-2-wins-best-game-at-fun-and-serious-festival-awards|archive-date=11 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Social/Family Game\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Australian Games Awards\n| Multiplayer/Online Title of the Year\n| {{Nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.australiangamesawards.com/news/|title=Your 2018 Winners|publisher=Australian Games Awards|date=19 December 2018|accessdate=8 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112043428/https://www.australiangamesawards.com/news/|archive-date=12 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\" | 2019\n| [[D.I.C.E. Awards]]\n| Online Game of the Year\n| {{Nom}}\n| style=\